  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>Enjoying wonderful valley views, the Charme Hotel Alexander is a luxurious four star hotel situated on the Mottolino side of Livigno. Refurbished in recent years, the hotel offers stylish décor, high standard accommodation, attentive service and an impressive spa for after ski relaxation.</span></p>
<h2><span>Close to lifts</span></h2>
<p><span>Located </span><span>on the Mottolino side of Livigno, the Charme Hotel Alexander has great proximity to the Teola lift just 200m away. </span><span>The free ski bus stops outside hotel to easily connect you with the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89}" title="Livigno">Livigno</a> town and other ski areas, so you can explore the </span>Alta Valtellina mountains in one of northern Italy’s most famous skiing resorts.</p>
<h2><span>Spa area</span></h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the snowy slopes of Livigno, the hotel's spa is the best place to relax. Soothe your weary muscles in the indoor saltwater lagoon which is heated to 32°C or unwind in the sauna, steam room or salt room. There is also a bio lagoon enriched with Himalayan salts and kept at 36°C - perfect for a moment of pure relaxation. The spa is payable locally per entry, although it is defiantly worth it for a little treat.</p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>Fuel up for the day at the varied breakfast buffet with a choice of sweet and savory products. When you return for the day delicious three course meal is served in the Panoramic restaurant, with a menu inspired by International and regional cuisine, you are in for a treat. If you are having a late start to the day or looking for an afternoon pick me up, the Bistro serves a range of snacks, hot and cold dishes and desserts. The bar is a lovely spot to enjoy an aperitif before dinner or a digestif before heading to bed - there's a selection of hot drinks, wines and grappas served until late.</p>]]></description>
